{
  "_notes": [
    "Reference template for universal_civ5_pipeline_spartan_artfix_v9.py using the refreshed Dahomey (2).zip PNG pack.",
    "Extract Dahomey (2).zip into C:/Repos/PNGtoDDSConverter/Input/. The ZIP already contains a Dahomey folder, so the final PNG paths should be C:/Repos/PNGtoDDSConverter/Input/Dahomey/*.png.",
    "mod_data_dir is intentionally omitted so check/build can run before the mod folder exists. Use --mod-data-dir in PowerShell when importing into an installed mod.",
    "Example mod_data_dir: C:/Users/ExampleUser/Documents/My Games/Sid Meier's Civilization 5/MODS/Dahomey BNW Custom Civ",
    "PowerShell check: py -3 .\\universal_civ5_pipeline_spartan_artfix_v9.py --config .\\Dahomey_art_reference_v2.json --check-only",
    "PowerShell build: py -3 .\\universal_civ5_pipeline_spartan_artfix_v9.py --config .\\Dahomey_art_reference_v2.json",
    "PowerShell import after reviewing previews: set $ModDataDir in Run_Dahomey_art_pipeline_v2.ps1, then run the import command using --mod-data-dir \"$ModDataDir\" --write-mod.",
    "Normal and alpha icons use the Spartan League v8 footprint: 0.65625 of each cell, so 256px cells get about 168px visible art.",
    "Unit flags are kept on the separate Civ V unit-flag profile, not the normal circular-icon footprint.",
    "Normal atlas index map: 0 civ, 1 leader, 2 DahomeyAmazon, 3 AgbaraWarrior, 4 RoyalCompound, 5 PalmOilPress, 6 WealthPalmSwordTrait, 7 Fearless, 8 FirstBlood, 9 TrophyTaker, 10 DahomeyDummyBuilding.",
    "This refreshed pack includes DahomeyLeader_Scene.png, so the leader scene now uses that source instead of falling back to DawnOfMan_Dahomey.png.",
    "This refreshed pack includes a distinct PalmOilPress_Icon.png, so the previous fallback-crop note no longer applies.",
    "SOURCE_RENAME_MAP.md is included in the source pack for provenance of the corrected filenames. It is not consumed by the pipeline."
  ],
